    "fetchedAt": "2026-07-02",
    "extractedFrom": "territory[id=US].fixedLine.nationalNumberPattern",
    "notes": "US fixedLine and mobile patterns are byte-identical upstream (NANP doesn't distinguish them by number range), so fixedLine's pattern was used for the general validation pattern. possibleLengths uses only the national length (10); the localOnly length (7, e.g. UAN-style 310-xxxx numbers) was intentionally dropped since DialSense only parses full E.164 numbers, where a local-only length is never valid."
  },
